The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 HCL Infosystems has earmarked an investment of Rs 70 crore in the next year to expand production capacity and strengthen its distribution and retail network in the country. The company recently commissioned its second manufacturing unit in Uttranchal. By the end of this fiscal, HCL aims to achieve a total manufacturing base of two million PCs from 1.2 million annually. The company has tied up with Tata Croma and other electronics retailers.

 The RBI has emphasised on the need for a policy on the financial inclusion of low-income households in its annual policy statement 2005-06 and mid-term review of annual policy statement 2005-06. The first phase of the national pilot project on financial inclusion has been completed and the Union Territory of Pondicherry has been fully covered under the programme.

 Alpa Laboratories Ltd has filed its draft red herring prospectus with the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) for an initial public offering of 95 lakh equity shares of Rs 10 each for cash at a premium, to be decided through book building. The issue will constitute 44.06 per cent of the fully diluted post-issue equity capital of the company.

 Balasore Alloys has received the Star Performer award for 2004-05 in product group (ferro alloys large enterprises) from the Engineering Export Promotion Council, eastern region. 

 The National Bank of Dubai (NBD) and HDFC Bank have joined hands to help conduct their banking transactions in UAE and India. The partnership, under the umbrella brand NBD-HDFC Bank NRI Services, will offer banking products and services such as joint account services, remittances and wealth management solutions.

 Pescarmona Group of Companies (PGC), a multinational privately-held group, has signed a final agreement to acquire GE Energys hydro business. The terms of the agreement were not disclosed. This acquisition excludes GE Energys operations in Norway and Sweden.

 Birla Sun Life Tax Relief 96 fund has been ranked second in the equity-linked savings schemes category, with a return of 48.56 per cent on a one-year return period. 

 Aptechs testing and certification arm, Attest, has received the ISO 27001 certificate from British Standards Institution for information security management system.

 Moser Baer has made its foray into the Indian home video market. The company will release video content on DVD and video CD formats using its proprietary and patented technology.

